ğŸš€ Deployment Guide
Backend Deployment on Render
Prerequisites
Render account

MongoDB Atlas account

GitHub repository with your code

Step-by-Step Deployment
Go to Render Dashboard

Create New Web Service

Click "New +" button

Select "Web Service"

Connect your GitHub repository

Configure Backend Service

yaml
Name: fast-food-backend
Environment: Node
Region: Ohio (or closest to your users)
Branch: main
Root Directory: backend
Build Command: npm install
Start Command: npm start
Set Environment Variables

env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=10000
MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_atlas_connection_string
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-app.onrender.com
Create Service

Click "Create Web Service"

Wait for deployment to complete

Frontend Deployment on Render
Create New Static Site

Click "New +" button

Select "Static Site"

Connect your GitHub repository

Configure Frontend Service

yaml
Name: fast-food-frontend
Root Directory: frontend
Build Command: npm run build
Publish Directory: frontend/dist
Set Environment Variables

env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-api.onrender.com/api
Create Static Site

Click "Create Static Site"

Wait for deployment

MongoDB Atlas Setup
Create MongoDB Atlas Account

Go to mongodb.com/cloud/atlas

Sign up for free

Create Cluster

Choose free tier (M0)

Select cloud provider and region

Create cluster

Database Access

Go to "Database Access"

Create new database user

Set username and password

Network Access

Go to "Network Access"

Add IP address: 0.0.0.0/0 (allow all IPs)

Get Connection String

Go to "Clusters"

Click "Connect"

Choose "Connect your application"

Copy connection string

Replace <password> with your database user password

ğŸ”§ Environment Variables
Backend (.env)
env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=10000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/fastfood?retryWrites=true&w=majority
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-frontend-app.onrender.com
Frontend (.env)
env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-api.onrender.com/api
VITE_APP_NAME=FastFood App
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
ğŸ“Š API Documentation
Base URL
text
https://your-backend-api.onrender.com/api
Endpoints
Menu
GET /menu - Get all menu items

GET /menu/:id - Get specific menu item

Orders
POST /orders - Create new order

GET /orders - Get all orders

GET /orders/:id - Get specific order

PATCH /orders/:id/status - Update order status

Payment
POST /payment/process - Process payment

Health
GET /health - Health check endpoint

ğŸš€ Local Development
Prerequisites
Node.js 18+

MongoDB (local or Atlas)

Installation
Clone the repository

bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/fast-food-app.git
cd fast-food-app
Install dependencies

bash
npm run install:all
Set up environment variables

bash
# Backend
cd backend
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your values

# Frontend
cd ../frontend
cp .env.example .env
Start development servers

bash
# Start both frontend and backend
npm run dev

# Or start separately
npm run dev:backend  # http://localhost:5000
npm run dev:frontend # http://localhost:3000
Seed database (optional)

bash
npm run seed:database
ğŸ§ª Testing
bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Run backend tests
npm run test:backend

# Run frontend tests
npm run test:frontend
ğŸ“ˆ Monitoring
The application includes health checks and monitoring:

bash
# Start monitoring
npm run monitor
Health check endpoint: GET /api/health

